
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class WebPortal {
    - version: String
    - url: String
}

class User {
    - username: String (unique)
    - email: String
    - password: String
}

class Building {
    - id: String (unique)
    - name: String
    - energyClass: Char (A/B/C/D)
    - address: String
    - yearOfConstruction: Integer
    - owner: User
}

class Entry {
    - name: String
    - isPublic: Boolean
    + addEntry()
}

class TextualEntry extends Entry {
    - content: String
}

class NumericEntry extends Entry {
    - value: Float
    - unit: String
}

class Image {
    - filename: String
    - isProfile: Boolean
}

class Comment {
    - text: String
    - author: User
    - building: Building
}

class Administrator extends User {
    - idCardNumber: String
}

class Search {
    - query: String
}

' Associations
User "1" --> "0..*" Building : owns
Building "1" --> "0..*" Entry : has
Building "1" --> "0..*" Image : has
Building "1" --> "0..*" Comment : commented on
User "1" --> "0..*" Comment : authored
Administrator "1" --> "1" User : extends
WebPortal "1" --> "0..*" User : contains
WebPortal "1" --> "0..*" Building : contains
WebPortal "1" --> "0..*" Search : provides

' Use Cases
usecase UC_Register_User as "Register User"
usecase UC_Confirm_Email as "Confirm Email"
usecase UC_Activate_User as "Activate User"
usecase UC_Login as "Login"
usecase UC_Create_Building as "Create Building"
usecase UC_Manage_Entries as "Manage Entries"
usecase UC_Comment_Building as "Comment on Building"
usecase UC_Search_Buildings as "Search Buildings"
usecase UC_Setup_User as "Setup User Account"
usecase UC_Delete_Comment as "Delete Comment"

' Actors
actor Visitor
actor RegisteredUser
actor Administrator

' Relationships between use cases and actors
RegisteredUser --> UC_Register_User
RegisteredUser --> UC_Confirm_Email
RegisteredUser --> UC_Activate_User
RegisteredUser --> UC_Login
RegisteredUser --> UC_Create_Building
RegisteredUser --> UC_Manage_Entries
RegisteredUser --> UC_Comment_Building

Visitor --> UC_Search_Buildings

Administrator --> UC_Setup_User
Administrator --> UC_Delete_Comment
Administrator --> UC_Login

UC_Register_User --> UC_Confirm_Email
UC_Confirm_Email --> UC_Activate_User
UC_Activate_User --> UC_Login

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements

- **Generalization**: `Administrator` inherits from `User`, reflecting their role as a special type of user.
- **Inheritance**: `TextualEntry` and `NumericEntry` inherit from the base class `Entry`.
- **Associations**:
  - A `User` can own multiple `Building`s.
  - A `Building` can have multiple `Entry`s and `Image`s.
  - A `Comment` is associated with both a `User` and a `Building`.
- **Use Cases & Actors**:
  - Use case generalizations like registration → confirmation → activation.
  - Administrators have extended privileges compared to regular users.
  - Visitors can only search for buildings.

---

### ✅ 10 Meaningful Use Cases with Assigned Actors

| Use Case | Actor |
|----------|-------|
| Register User | Visitor / Potential User |
| Confirm Email | RegisteredUser |
| Activate User | System (implicitly) |
| Login | RegisteredUser, Administrator |
| Create Building | RegisteredUser |
| Manage Entries | RegisteredUser |
| Comment on Building | RegisteredUser |
| Search Buildings | Visitor, RegisteredUser |
| Setup User Account | Administrator |
| Delete Comment | Administrator |

